{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vx9FActZvVu6PzWLHbXEX2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is my full report.\n\n---\n\n## Search Results\n\n### 1. StepML Model Artifact JSON Files\n\nAll model artifacts are located under the `BLIS-research` repository at:\n\n```\n/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round2/\n```\n\nThere are two artifact formats discovered:\n\n#### Version 1 (single-regime, \"step_time\" key)\n\nFound only under `idea-2-regime-ensemble/h1-kv-regime-models/output/artifacts/` with `_single.json` suffix. These have a flat `\"step_time\"` object with a single linear model (no regime switching).\n\n**Files (5 total):**\n- `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round2/idea-2-regime-ensemble/h1-kv-regime-models/output/artifacts/llama-2-7b_tp1_single.json`\n- `.../codellama-34b_tp2_single.json`\n- `.../llama-2-70b_tp4_single.json`\n- `.../llama-2-70b-hf_tp4_single.json`\n- `.../mixtral-8x7b-v0-1_tp2_single.json`\n\n**Example structure** (llama-2-7b_tp1_single.json):\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"step_time\": {\n    \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n    \"intercept\": -38.80,\n    \"feature_coefficients\": {\n      \"prefill_tokens\": 0.220,\n      \"decode_tokens\": 8.014,\n      \"num_prefill_reqs\": 106.99,\n      \"num_decode_reqs\": 8.014\n    }\n  },\n  \"step_overhead_us\": 3896.76,\n  \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 0,\n  \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 0,\n  \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 0\n}\n```\n\n#### Version 2 (regime-switching, \"step_time_regimes\" key)\n\nFound across both ideas. These contain a `\"step_time_regimes\"` array with conditional regime selection and per-regime linear models.\n\n**Idea 1 (Bayesian Calibration) -- 2-regime piecewise artifacts (23 files):**\n\nLocated in three directories:\n- `idea-1-bayesian-calibration/h1-piecewise-steptime/output/artifacts/` (5 base artifacts, `_piecewise.json`)\n- `idea-1-bayesian-calibration/h4-model-generalization/output/lomo_artifacts/` (5 LOMO artifacts)\n- `idea-1-bayesian-calibration/h5-workload-generalization/output/lowo_artifacts/` (13 LOWO artifacts)\n\nExample (llama-2-7b_tp1_piecewise.json): Two regimes -- `decode_only` (prefill_tokens == 0) and `mixed_batch` (fallback). Features: prefill_tokens, decode_tokens, prefill_x_decode.\n\n**Idea 2 (Regime Ensemble) -- 3-regime artifacts (49 files):**\n\nLocated in five directories:\n- `idea-2-regime-ensemble/h1-kv-regime-models/output/artifacts/` (10 files: 5 `_regime.json` + 5 `_single.json`)\n- `idea-2-regime-ensemble/h3-secondary-method-calibration/output/calibrated_artifacts/` (5 calibrated `_regime.json`)\n- `idea-2-regime-ensemble/h4-model-generalization/output/lomo_artifacts/` (5 LOMO `_regime.json`)\n- `idea-2-regime-ensemble/h5-workload-generalization/output/lowo_artifacts/` (18 LOWO `_regime.json`, per model x workload)\n- `idea-2-regime-ensemble/h2-blis-e2e-validation/output/e2e_summary_regime.json` (1 summary)\n\nExample structure (llama-2-7b_tp1_regime.json, H1 base artifact):\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": 2,\n  \"step_time_regimes\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"decode_only\",\n      \"condition\": {\"feature\": \"prefill_tokens\", \"op\": \"==\", \"value\": 0},\n      \"model\": {\n        \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n        \"intercept\": -37.37,\n        \"feature_coefficients\": {\n          \"decode_tokens\": 7.95,\n          \"num_decode_reqs\": 7.95\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"mixed_light\",\n      \"condition\": {\"feature\": \"prefill_tokens\", \"op\": \"<\", \"value\": 256},\n      \"model\": {\n        \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n        \"intercept\": -77.98,\n        \"feature_coefficients\": {\n          \"prefill_tokens\": 28.71, \"decode_tokens\": 8.24,\n          \"num_prefill_reqs\": 48.63, \"num_decode_reqs\": 8.24,\n          \"prefill_x_decode\": -0.16, \"prefill_sq\": -0.81\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"step_overhead_us\": 3896.76,\n  \"output_token_processing_time_us\": 0,\n  \"scheduling_processing_time_us\": 0,\n  \"preemption_processing_time_us\": 0\n}\n```\n\nThe **calibrated** H3 artifacts additionally include `scheduling_processing_time_us` and a `queueing_time` object (e.g., 202us for llama-2-7b).\n\nThe **LOMO** H4 artifacts include 3 regimes (decode_only, mixed_light, mixed_heavy with null condition as fallback) and KV features (kv_sum, kv_max, kv_mean, kv_std, decode_x_kv_mean).\n\nThe **E2E summary** (`e2e_summary_regime.json`):\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"regime\",\n  \"n_completed\": 10,\n  \"n_skipped\": 0,\n  \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": 427.81,\n  \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": 31905.77,\n  \"mean_itl_error_pct\": 33.64,\n  \"experiments_below_10pct\": 1\n}\n```\n\n**Models covered across all artifacts:** llama-2-7b (TP1), codellama-34b (TP2), llama-2-70b (TP4), llama-2-70b-hf (TP4), mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 (TP2).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Directories Named \"round2\" or Containing \"idea-2\"\n\nSix directories found:\n\n| Directory | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round2/` | Main Round 2 research directory (BLIS-research repo) |\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round2/idea-2-regime-ensemble/` | Idea 2 within Round 2 |\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round1/idea-2-analytical-decomposition/` | Idea 2 from Round 1 (analytical decomposition) |\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/idea-2-total-context-model/` | Idea 2 for Round 3 (total context model) |\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round3-idea-1-trace-replay/hypotheses/h-stepml/round3/idea-2-total-context-model/` | Same Round 3 idea-2 in worktree |\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round3-idea-1-trace-replay/hypotheses/h-stepml/round1/idea-2-analytical-decomposition/` | Round 1 idea-2 in worktree |\n\nNote: There is no `round2/` directory in the worktree -- Round 2 content exists only in the `BLIS-research` repo.\n\n---\n\n### 3. FINDINGS Files Under hypotheses/h-stepml/\n\n**19 FINDINGS files found across both repos.** Below are all unique files (some are duplicated across the BLIS-research repo and the worktree; the worktree copies only contain Round 1 content).\n\n#### Round 1 FINDINGS\n\n| File | Brief Summary |\n|---|---|\n| `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/hypotheses/h-stepml/round1/FINDINGS_ROUND1.md` | Comprehensive Round 1 summary. Per-experiment XGBoost achieved 34% MAPE (2x better than blackbox). Missing per-request KV features identified as primary blocker. No BLIS E2E validation performed. |\n| `.../round1/idea-1-tree-ensemble/h1-features/FINDINGS.md` | 30 physics-informed features + Ridge regression. 92.1% per-experiment MAPE; global model: 301.7%. |\n| `.../round1/idea-1-tree-ensemble/h2-model/FINDINGS.md` | XGBoost per-experiment: 34% avg MAPE, 5/16 under 15%. Best single result. |\n| `.../round1/idea-1-tree-ensemble/h3-generalization/FINDINGS.md` | LOMO: 2559.7%, LOWO: 109.7%. Cross-model transfer fails catastrophically. |\n| `.../round1/idea-2-analytical-decomposition/h1-features/FINDINGS.md` | 4-component FLOPs decomposition. 0/4 components exceed 0.8 Pearson r. decode_attention_flops = 0 (structural incompleteness). |\n| `.../round1/idea-2-analytical-decomposition/h2-model/FINDINGS.md` | Learned correction factors: 78.7% MAPE -- worse than blackbox (70.4%). Pathological compensation (factor=39.5 on zero signal). |\n\nThe worktree at `stepml-worktrees/round3-idea-1-trace-replay` contains copies of the Round 1 FINDINGS plus:\n- `/Users/