{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_017HLXXLSQ96yA8DRFfYGjhi","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue. When alpha/beta are all zeros AND no model config folder is provided, it fatally exits. The StepML path bypasses alpha/beta but BLIS still detects them as all-zero and tries to activate roofline. I need to either:\n1. Pass non-zero dummy alpha/beta coefficients, or  \n2. Fix the fallback logic to check for StepML before the all-zero check\n\nThe simplest fix: pass non-zero dummy coefficients (like `1,0,0`) since the StepML model overrides them anyway. Let me update the experiment script:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ea608f4-4aa5-4264-9119-cf38f8fb2f5c","uuid":"bb2223e3-b5f4-495f-9c71-ad91da14a62b"}
