{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01VVn9ejTPNC25cUbfXYm8DV","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**Key findings so far:**\n1. **Trace replay reduced E2E error from 427.8% to 56.2%** (7.6x improvement) — confirming workload-spec was a major error source.\n2. **TTFT reduced from 31,906% to 78.8%** (405x improvement) — TTFT was indeed dominated by workload-spec mismatch.\n3. **ITL improved from 33.6% to 9.5%** — trace replay also helps ITL by providing correct request sizes.\n4. **H3 reveals the workload-spec parameters are actually very close** (< 1% rate/duration/count errors) — meaning the TTFT error in Round 2 was NOT from arrival rate mismatch but from BLIS's workload *generation* process (how it samples request sizes from the spec).\n5. **E2E still at 56% even with trace replay** — BLIS consistently under-predicts E2E by ~50-60%, suggesting the step-time model systematically under-estimates real step times.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nThe results are very informative. Now let me write the FINDINGS.md for each sub-hypothesis and the summary. The results show BLIS consistently under-predicts E2E (all BLIS values are ~40-50% of ground truth), suggesting the step-time model is too fast. Let me write all three FINDINGS.md files."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ea608f4-4aa5-4264-9119-cf38f8fb2f5c","uuid":"a3b18a85-8d44-457a-931b-a32074d0ebfe"}
